cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use NeoRAG in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "NeoRAG: Neurosymbolic Answer Validation with Self-Refinement for Retrieval-Augmented Generation"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2025-05-18"
authors:
  - family-names: Knoll
    given-names: Carsten
    affiliation: "Professur Grundlagen der Elektrotechnik, Technische Universität Dresden"
    email: carsten.knoll@posteo.de
license: GPL-3.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/cknoll/neorag"
abstract: >
  NeoRAG is a small, open-source RAG prototype that demonstrates neurosymbolic
  answer validation with a closed self-refinement loop and a pluggable LLM backend.
  It serves as the technical Vorarbeit (preliminary work) for research question FF2
  of the SoFAKTA proposal: lightweight SHACL, Pydantic, and groundedness constraints
  in a configurable self-refinement loop as a hallucination-mitigation strategy
  compatible with local-first, sovereignty-preserving deployments.
keywords:
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - RAG
  - neurosymbolic AI
  - SHACL
  - answer validation
  - self-refinement
  - hallucination mitigation
  - data sovereignty
